description.p:
According to a sixth aspect, the invention relates to a method for manufacturing an ornamental component, said ornamental component having a through hole allowing said ornamental component to be strung on an elongated member of a bracelet and / or necklace, said through hole defining a through hole axis, the method comprising the steps of:
providing a self-supporting housing, having an through hole, wherein said through hole comprises a first opening at a first side of the self-supporting housing and a second opening at a second side of the self-supporting housing;
inserting through said first opening of said self-supporting housing a first tubular element having a through hole;
inserting through said second opening of said self-supporting housing a locking element having a through hole, said locking element comprising an engagement portion for being positioned inside said through hole of said self-supporting housing; and
attaching said engagement portion of said locking element to said first tubular element.

claim.claim-text:
13. A method for manufacturing an ornamental component (100,300), said ornamental component (100,300) having a through hole allowing said ornamental component (100,300) to be strung on an elongated member of a bracelet and / or necklace, said through hole defining a through hole axis (104,304), comprising the steps of:
• providing a self-supporting housing (101,301), having a through hole (350), wherein said through hole (350) comprises a first opening (151,351) at a first side of the self-supporting housing (101,301) and a second opening (152,352) at a second side of the self-supporting housing (101,301);
• assembling an insert assembly (102,103,370) comprising a first tubular element (102,302) having a through hole that at least partly forms said through hole of said ornamental component (100,300), and a gripping element (103,303) for frictionally gripping said elongated member of a bracelet and / or a necklace; and
• inserting said insert assembly (101,102, 370) in said through hole (350) of said housing (101,301);
characterized in that said first tubular element (102,302) comprises a first circumferential opening (426) extending along the through hole axis (104,304), and wherein said gripping element (103,303) comprises a first gripping portion (533), for frictionally gripping said elongated member of said bracelet and / or necklace, and a tubular portion (531), wherein said first gripping portion (533) is protruding from an inner surface (536) of said tubular portion (531), and wherein the step of assembling said insert assembly (102,103,370) comprises pulling said gripping element (103,303) around said first tubular element (102,302) until said first gripping portion (533) is aligned with said first circumferential opening (426), whereby said first gripping portion (533) extends through said first circumferential opening (426) and a part of said inner surface (536) of said tubular portion (531) rests upon a part of the outer surface of said first tubular element (102,302) thereby securing said gripping element (103,303) to said first tubular element (102,302).
